MERN
M: MongoDB 
E: Express.js 
R: React 
N: Node.js

React for Frontend (Client Side)
Node.js and Express.js for Backend (Server Side)
MongoDB for Database Management

Terms: Rendered

-Frontend
--So frontend is the visual interface to which an user interact with, responsible for presenting information and taking users input.
--It is divided into 3 parts or we can say tech HTML(Structuring), CSS(Styling), Javascript(Interactive)
--Morden Frameworks like React, Angular, Vue.js are all built upon on JavaScript
--React allow us to create reusable UI components, manage application state effectively, and build highly ineteractive and performant Single Page Applications (SPA).

-Backend
--It powers the Frontend, Manage Business Logic, Data Processing, Server Management, and communicate with the database.
--For the backend, we will be using Node.js, a JavaScript runtime environment that allows us to run JavaScript code on the server. 
Paired with the Express.js framework, Node.js provides a robust and efficient platform for building web servers and APIs. 
This allows developers to use JavaScript across the entire stack, simplifying development and improving code consistency.

-Database
--It is used to store data for application use.
--We will be using MongoDB a NoSQL database for storing complex data format and scalablity.

Frontend: React
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Database: MongoDB
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Routing: React Router
State Management: Redux Toolkit (introduced as an option for complex state)
API Interaction: Axios
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
Development Tools: VS Code, npm/yarn, Git, Browser Developer Tools, Postman/Insomnia

                  
